Global Video Surveillance Storage Device Market Insights
Video Surveillance Storage Device Market size was valued at USD 5.3 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 10.2 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Video Surveillance Storage Device Market Overview
The global video surveillance storage device market is experiencing significant growth, projected to reach a market value of USD 25.2 billion by 2027, growing at a CAGR of 22.5% from 2023. This market growth is attributed to the increasing demand for high-resolution surveillance systems and the need for enhanced data storage solutions to support large volumes of video footage. As businesses and governments continue to prioritize security, video surveillance storage devices play a pivotal role in ensuring the efficient storage, management, and retrieval of video data. Factors such as the growing adoption of smart cities, infrastructure development, and rising concerns over security are contributing to the expansion of this market. The shift towards cloud-based storage and advancements in artificial intelligence (AI) also present significant opportunities for market players to innovate and meet evolving consumer demands.

